<subSubSection pageId="61" pageNumber="62" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="61.[151,1437,152,402]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,318,338,364]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aldrich, Suigen" authorityYear="1925" box="[626,765,338,364]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dexia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ventralis">
<emphasis box="[626,647,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[662,765,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">ventralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but is distinguished from it in having 3 presutural and 4 postsutural dorsocentral setae, and abdominal tergite 3 with a complete row of marginal setae.
</paragraph>
